Description: Intact small wheel-made pottery jar, made in red-brown Nile silt fabric. The exterior bears a red wash or self slip.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Great Temenos, Vicinity (outside) of the north-west corner (Hogarth excavations 1903)
Curator's comments: Excavated from the area of the north-west corner of the 'Great Temenos' by Hogarth in 1903. dated by Edgar to the 7th to 5th century BC, but probably 'nearer the earlier limit', and he cites Saite parallels (Edgar 1905, 125, Fig.5).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IB.047) (Phase 3)
